Verizon Family
Verizon Family Privacy Policy for Kids
What is Verizon Family?
Verizon Family (previously called Smart Family) lets parents (known in the app as Guardians) and other trusted adults (known as Members) keep an eye on kids' phones and tablets. It helps families find each other's devices, and depending on your Guardians’ plan, may include tools that let your Guardians and others they allow set screen time and usage limits, approve contacts, block certain websites and apps, pause the internet, see who and when you call and text over the Verizon network and what websites you visit and apps you use, and monitor your driving activity. Verizon Family also has Safe Walk, which lets you quickly send your device location to your emergency contacts. Your Guardian can also turn on Roadside Assistance so that you can get help if you have a problem with a car you are in, like a flat tire or a dead battery.
What information do we collect about you?
When a Guardian adds you to a Verizon Family account, we may collect from them your name, photo, birthday, trusted and emergency contacts, and info about the Verizon Family features they want to use, like whether they want to block certain websites or apps, and if you are a driver or passenger (if you have turned on driving insights monitoring). If your phone or tablet is connected to the Verizon network, we collect your device location using our wireless network, information about who and when you are calling and texting over the Verizon wireless network, how much data you are using, and information about your phone or tablet, like its phone number and certain device identifiers.
If you download the Verizon Family companion app and give us permission, we may also collect your device’s precise location using GPS, online activity, the contacts saved on your phone or tablet, and motion activity that shows if you are walking, running, biking, or riding in a car. We also collect other information about your device, like the device type, the version of the Verizon Family app you are using, the features you use in the app, and other device identifiers and IP address. This information is used to provide the services requested by your Guardian.
We will also collect a PIN from you which you can use to cancel an SOS alert that you may activate during a Safe Walk session. If you enable driving insights, we will collect information about where you are and other information like your trip route and distance; how fast the vehicle traveled; how the vehicle braked, accelerated, and cornered; and potential crashes. This information is used to create a driving score for each trip you take. If your Guardian says you are a driver, we will also collect info about whether you are using your phone when the car is moving and use that to help calculate your overall driving score.
If your Guardian has turned on Roadside Assistance, and you request help, we will collect your name, phone number, info about your car, the address where you are asking for help, and the service you need so that our Roadside Assistance provider can help you.
If your phone or tablet is connected to the Verizon network, we will also collect an E-911 address to help with emergency response in case you need help.
How does Verizon Family use this information?
Verizon Family only collects from you the information we need to make Verizon Family work and to improve it. We never sell kids’ information or use it to show them ads.
Who does Verizon Family share this information with?
Verizon Family shares  information about you with other people on the Verizon Family account and with
companies that help us provide Verizon Family
1
. These companies can only use your information to provide and help us improve Verizon Family and they must delete your information when they no longer need it to provide the service. We don't share information we collect through Verizon Family for any other purpose.
Close
×
1.
Companies That Help Us Provide Verizon Family
We share information about you, including where you are, with companies called Here Technologies and Mapbox so they can show where you are on a map in the Verizon Family apps.  We also share certain identifiers from your phone or tablet with Google Analytics so it can help us see how our apps are working and with PubNub to deliver alerts that Guardians set about your location or activity. Information about your online activity on your phone or tablet may also be shared with a company called Cloudflare if a VPN is turned on to monitor the websites you visit and the apps you use or block you from visiting certain websites or apps. And if driving activity monitoring is turned on, we share your location, motion data, and information about phone usage while driving with a company called Cambridge Mobile Telematics who provides driving scores. If your Guardian enables Roadside Assistance and you request help, we will share your name, phone number, info about your car, the address where you are asking for help, and the service you need with our Roadside Assistance provider, Signature Motor Club.
What control do I have over the information you have about me?
When your Guardian adds you to their Verizon Family account, they have to agree to let us collect some information about you. They can also invite you to download the Verizon Family Companion app. If you download the app, you’ll be asked to let Verizon Family collect some information about you, like your location, how you’re moving (like walking, biking, running, or in a vehicle), and the contacts on your phone or tablet. You’ll also be asked to allow Verizon Family to install a VPN, which lets your Guardians and others they allow see what websites and apps you’re using, block certain ones, and even pause the internet.
You can turn off some permissions, like the VPN and the sharing of your motion activity or your contacts, in your phone or tablet’s settings. If you uninstall the VPN, some features that let your Guardians and others they allow see your web and app activity may be turned off. But, if you use an Android, your screen time info might still be collected depending on your settings. You can also change your location permission in your device settings, but Verizon Family will still get your estimated location from the wireless network if you have a Verizon device. You can turn off driving insights monitoring in your Verizon Family app’s settings.
If you are using an Android phone or tablet, and depending on your Guardians’ Verizon Family plan, you may be asked to turn on Accessibility settings for your Verizon Family Companion app. If you turn on Accessibility settings, you won’t be able to delete the Verizon Family Companion app or turn off the VPN without first asking your Guardian for a PIN.
If you delete the Verizon Family Companion app, Verizon Family will stop collecting your GPS location, how you’re moving, online activity, and driving info. But Verizon Family will still get your estimated location from the Verizon wireless network.
To stop all information sharing by Verizon Family, your Guardian needs to remove your profile from their Verizon Family app. Verizon will continue to collect information to provide wireless service to your device.
How long does Verizon Family keep the information it collects about me?
We only keep the information for as long as we need it to provide the Verizon Family service to you. When your Guardians don’t want to use Verizon Family any longer and unsubscribe from Verizon Family, or delete your profile from their account, Verizon Family deletes the information we have about you.
Do I have specific rights under any state privacy laws?
Some states give you the right to see what data we have about you and ask to have it deleted or corrected. If you would like to see the data we have about you or ask to have it deleted or corrected, talk to your parents. They can see, delete, and make changes to some information we have about you directly in their Verizon Family app or can make a request on your behalf. You can also call (800) 333-3972 to make a request to see the data we have about you or ask to have it deleted or, if you are 13 years or older, you can make a request through our
Verizon privacy inquiries form
.
What if I want more information about how Verizon Family treats information about me?
If you want to know more about how Verizon Family uses your information, view our full
Verizon Family Privacy Policy
with your parents. You or your parents can also email us at
verizonfamily@verizonwireless.com
.
